WEBVTT

00:00.023 --> 00:01.835
<i>Previously, on</i>
"This Is Us"...

00:01.921 --> 00:05.493
RANDALL: Mom is suffering
from cognitive impairment.

00:05.578 --> 00:07.485
Mom asked me
not to tell you guys.

00:07.570 --> 00:09.953
She didn't want to add
any more stress to your plates.

00:10.038 --> 00:11.998
Let me take care of Jack
this weekend.

00:12.083 --> 00:14.001
I need to spend time
with my son.

00:14.086 --> 00:15.337
(imitating Chewbacca)

00:15.662 --> 00:16.929
You like it?

00:18.389 --> 00:19.406
MADISON:
Hey, Kate.

00:19.554 --> 00:22.229
Uh. It's Madison.
I slept with Kevin!

00:22.314 --> 00:23.500
(Kevin groans)

00:23.585 --> 00:25.414
RANDALL:
I've been anxious for so long.

00:25.780 --> 00:28.195
Beth thinks
I should see a therapist.

00:28.300 --> 00:30.382
Well, maybe you should.

00:32.838 --> 00:34.804
[♪ ♪]

00:34.900 --> 00:36.148
(door opens)

00:36.233 --> 00:37.828
Sorry I'm late, guys.

00:37.913 --> 00:39.656
I got out of there

00:39.741 --> 00:41.781
just as soon as I could.

00:41.866 --> 00:43.951
‐Hi. Hi.
‐Hi.

00:44.524 --> 00:45.664
JACK:
Report Card Day.

00:45.749 --> 00:47.320
‐ They've been waiting.
‐ Report Card Day.

00:47.404 --> 00:49.906
‐ Let's... do this, huh?
‐ (Rebecca giggles)

00:51.223 --> 00:52.641
Oh.

00:52.795 --> 00:54.906
‐ Oh, that is a serious face.
‐ REBECCA: Oh, yeah.

00:54.991 --> 00:56.576
‐ Bec, this is bad news.
‐ Mm‐ hmm.

00:56.729 --> 00:58.421
I think, maybe,
could it be his...

00:58.506 --> 01:00.841
straight‐ A streak is over?

01:01.064 --> 01:03.792
(gasps)
Oh, an A‐ minus in geometry.

01:03.877 --> 01:05.750
Oh, you are so grounded.

01:05.835 --> 01:07.296
I'm putting too much time
into Mathletes

01:07.380 --> 01:09.046
and not enough time
into actual math.

01:09.131 --> 01:10.681
JACK: Oh, no, hey,
come on, this is great, pal.

01:10.765 --> 01:11.961
‐ Really. Forget it.
‐ REBECCA: Hey.

01:12.045 --> 01:13.734
‐ Bug, are you okay?
‐ Wait, so...

01:13.868 --> 01:16.382
she could be bluffing.

01:16.651 --> 01:18.778
‐ Is she bluffing?
‐ Is she?

01:20.886 --> 01:22.136
Huh.

01:22.228 --> 01:24.480
Improvements in biology...

01:24.757 --> 01:26.297
‐ and civics.
‐ Yeah, Kate, this is great.

01:26.381 --> 01:29.124
‐ What's wrong?
‐ Stuart broke up with me.

01:29.235 --> 01:30.906
‐ Aw, hon...
‐ No.

01:30.991 --> 01:33.570
I need to be alone.
Don't follow me.

01:33.697 --> 01:35.218
‐ Katie girl...
‐ No, no, I...

01:35.734 --> 01:37.070
‐ I will handle that.
‐ Sure.

01:37.155 --> 01:40.249
Let's do Kevin quickly,
and then I'll go upstairs.

01:40.580 --> 01:43.015
Oh, that's a very smug mug, sir.

01:43.100 --> 01:44.643
Can it be...?

01:45.538 --> 01:46.976
Two As, baby.

01:47.061 --> 01:48.273
What?

01:49.968 --> 01:51.585
Yeah, in P.E. and art.

01:51.670 --> 01:53.882
The rest are Cs and two Ds.

01:54.093 --> 01:56.846
"Disruptive in class."
"Arrives late."

01:56.930 --> 01:59.148
"Needs to be center
of attention"? Kevin.

01:59.233 --> 02:00.724
Two As are two As.

02:00.809 --> 02:03.185
Mom said I'd get five dollars
for every "A."

02:03.421 --> 02:05.618
Bet you five bucks you
don't know what that adds up to.

02:05.703 --> 02:08.491
I'm gonna buy an entire box of
baseball cards with my winnings.

02:08.577 --> 02:10.191
Yeah, well,
I'm gonna contest my grade.

02:10.276 --> 02:11.527
That'll be an "A" by next week.

02:11.611 --> 02:13.165
You know, Randall,
it wouldn't hurt you to...

02:13.249 --> 02:14.529
to lighten up on yourself.

02:14.614 --> 02:16.825
No way.
I'm going to fix this.

02:21.133 --> 02:23.885
Hey. Ten bucks. American.

02:23.970 --> 02:25.972
RANDALL: The second I talk
to Mrs. Hollins,

02:26.197 --> 02:27.531
it'll be up to an "A."

02:27.630 --> 02:29.047
Hey, babe?

02:29.132 --> 02:31.140
Randall is getting worse.

02:31.530 --> 02:34.367
Do we need to talk to someone,
like a guidance counsellor

02:34.454 --> 02:36.217
‐ or a...? ‐ No, come on,
he's just, he's wound up tight.

02:36.301 --> 02:37.887
All right?
He needs to blow off some steam.

02:37.971 --> 02:39.632
Blow off steam?

02:39.722 --> 02:42.109
Don't worry about it.
I got it. Go on.

02:42.202 --> 02:43.578
Okay.

02:45.812 --> 02:47.772
(footfalls approaching)

02:50.640 --> 02:52.009
Everything okay?

02:52.188 --> 02:54.437
Uh, yeah, why?

02:54.612 --> 02:57.364
I don't know,
just thought you'd be

02:57.546 --> 03:00.409
a little more refreshed
after a weekend at the cabin.

03:00.493 --> 03:03.460
Ah. Um,
Mom's getting the results

03:03.545 --> 03:05.140
for her MRI this afternoon,

03:05.225 --> 03:07.242
and I can tell
she's a little nervous.

03:07.667 --> 03:10.002
Just really hate
not being there in person.

03:10.086 --> 03:12.859
But, hey, that's something
you could talk about in therapy,

03:12.944 --> 03:14.981
‐ right?
‐ Yeah.

03:15.605 --> 03:17.218
I'm so proud of you.

03:17.309 --> 03:19.227
This is a big step.

03:19.390 --> 03:21.309
It's not that big of a deal.

03:22.096 --> 03:23.447
All right.

03:23.532 --> 03:25.575
‐ No big deal.
‐ Mm‐ hmm.

03:26.019 --> 03:28.950
Uh, so, hey, listen, you know,
Annie's birthday is coming up,

03:29.035 --> 03:32.427
‐ and I was thinking... ‐ Have you
still got that organic beeswax balm

03:32.543 --> 03:35.372
‐ you keep talking about?
‐ Hey, out of my purse, man.

03:35.474 --> 03:37.670
What are you...?
Aah! What?

03:37.755 --> 03:39.782
‐ And I was thinking...
‐ Thank you.

03:39.866 --> 03:41.993
That we could get her
the iPhone.

03:43.000 --> 03:45.834
We agreed:
no iPhones until junior high.

03:45.919 --> 03:49.076
I know. But, you know,
she's so cute when she begs.

03:49.161 --> 03:51.225
‐ Mm‐ hmm. ‐ You know,
the Force is strong with that one.

03:51.309 --> 03:53.436
But it is stronger in us.

03:53.521 --> 03:55.439
At least it is now.

03:55.566 --> 03:56.896
RANDALL:
Mmm.

03:57.419 --> 03:59.380
I love your lip balm.

04:00.052 --> 04:02.762
I love your face.

04:03.043 --> 04:05.087
[♪ ♪]

04:06.481 --> 04:08.650
(growling playfully):
Yeah...

04:10.563 --> 04:12.648
‐ Hey.
‐ Morning.

04:12.732 --> 04:13.816
You're up early.

04:13.900 --> 04:14.989
Coffee's fresh.

04:15.074 --> 04:16.206
Hi.

04:16.569 --> 04:18.654
‐ (crying)
‐ Hi.

04:18.738 --> 04:20.613
My goodness.

04:20.699 --> 04:22.826
Someone was asleep
when Mommy got home last night

04:22.911 --> 04:24.730
from the cabin.

04:25.825 --> 04:28.497
Um, I know we didn't really get
a chance to talk last night,

04:28.581 --> 04:29.790
so I'll start.

04:29.874 --> 04:31.000
I'm sorry.

04:31.084 --> 04:32.334
(Jack coos)

04:32.418 --> 04:33.919
For everything.

04:34.003 --> 04:36.465
I said what I said out of...

04:36.550 --> 04:38.841
fear and‐ and worry
and exhaustion,

04:38.925 --> 04:41.552
and if I could take it all back,
I would.

04:41.989 --> 04:43.615
But...

04:44.920 --> 04:47.419
This weekend was a real godsend.

04:48.295 --> 04:50.723
So without further ado,

04:50.900 --> 04:54.505
would you please follow
me and Jack to the garage?

04:54.732 --> 04:57.154
We have a surprise for you.

04:57.239 --> 04:59.741
All right, you're gonna have
to use your imagination here.

05:00.037 --> 05:02.122
But I was thinking...

05:02.357 --> 05:04.366
we turn the garage...

05:04.778 --> 05:07.354
into a music studio, huh?

05:07.857 --> 05:09.487
Now... here, take him...

05:09.572 --> 05:11.323
it's not all...

05:11.525 --> 05:13.610
up to scale...

05:14.698 --> 05:17.450
But, uh, this would be...
the microphone.

05:17.792 --> 05:19.835
Testing, one, two, three.

05:19.920 --> 05:21.339
‐ So, stay with me.
‐ Toby.

05:21.424 --> 05:23.425
This is the pièce de résistance.
Ready?

05:23.530 --> 05:24.864
Toby, please stop.

05:25.103 --> 05:27.647
‐ (sighs)
‐ Please.

05:28.971 --> 05:31.187
I really appreciate
what you're trying to do.

05:32.134 --> 05:33.581
But, you know,

05:33.666 --> 05:35.876
after one weekend...

05:36.232 --> 05:38.526
I'm just having tr...

05:38.943 --> 05:40.479
This is very nice.

05:40.820 --> 05:42.589
It's a very sweet gesture.

05:42.822 --> 05:45.378
I‐ I just,
I'm gonna need some time.

05:45.658 --> 05:47.118
Okay.

05:48.062 --> 05:49.925
(phone chimes, buzzes)

05:52.008 --> 05:53.426
What?

05:54.041 --> 05:55.479
Is everything okay?
Is it your mom?

05:55.564 --> 05:56.690
No, it's Madison.

05:56.932 --> 05:58.839
(sighs)
She slept with Kevin,

05:58.924 --> 06:01.259
so she wants to have brunch
so she can apologize.

06:01.956 --> 06:03.541
I'm sorry, I know
that we're kind of in the middle

06:03.625 --> 06:05.877
of a thing right now,
but permission to react?

06:06.179 --> 06:07.089
Yeah.

06:07.255 --> 06:08.429
What?!

06:08.514 --> 06:10.016
(Jack coos)

06:14.604 --> 06:15.979
REBECCA:
How was your trip

06:16.064 --> 06:17.425
with your brother
and your sister?

06:17.510 --> 06:18.901
Oh, the trip was great.

06:18.986 --> 06:20.737
You know, very peaceful,
lot of bonding.

06:20.829 --> 06:22.559
‐ Exactly what I needed.
It was wonderful. ‐ Yeah.

06:22.643 --> 06:23.832
‐ Nice.
‐ How are you?

06:23.917 --> 06:24.932
I'm good.

06:25.017 --> 06:27.018
Well, that's great.
I mean, you look great.

06:27.700 --> 06:29.285
‐ I do?
‐ Yes, you do.

06:29.369 --> 06:30.629
Well, thank you.

06:30.808 --> 06:32.757
Wonderful, actually.

06:36.380 --> 06:38.049
They told you, didn't they?

06:39.016 --> 06:41.810
What? Told me what? No.

06:42.027 --> 06:43.236
Kevin.

06:44.675 --> 06:46.368
Randall let it slip.

06:47.767 --> 06:49.260
Sweetheart, I'm sorry.

06:49.345 --> 06:51.807
‐ No.
‐ No, I, I wanted to tell you

06:51.891 --> 06:53.652
‐ in person myself.
‐ No, no, no, no. Listen,

06:53.851 --> 06:55.769
don't you worry about me,
you understand?

06:55.853 --> 06:57.813
I'm... I'm here
to take care of you.

06:57.897 --> 07:00.254
All right?
How are you really feeling?

07:00.339 --> 07:02.568
I know you have some MRI results
coming back today, right?

07:02.652 --> 07:04.820
‐ Mm‐ hmm. I'm‐ I'm good, though.
‐ Okay.

07:04.904 --> 07:08.615
I'm good. I'm a little anxious
about today, I'm not gonna lie,

07:08.699 --> 07:12.878
but it's funny, somehow all
of this bad news has sort of...

07:13.003 --> 07:14.644
freed me up.

07:14.729 --> 07:16.620
Carpe diem and all that.

07:17.101 --> 07:18.597
‐ Hey. How you doing?
‐ Hey.

07:18.682 --> 07:19.902
Ah. Good.

07:19.987 --> 07:21.019
‐ Good.
‐ Yeah?

07:21.104 --> 07:23.144
‐ All things considered, yeah.
‐ Okay.

07:23.229 --> 07:24.897
Great. Well... Oh, man.

07:25.112 --> 07:26.572
What‐ what‐ what are you guys
doing today?

07:26.656 --> 07:30.106
Oh. We actually
were planning on going to visit

07:30.191 --> 07:33.778
some of those, um...
old‐ fashioned record stores.

07:33.863 --> 07:35.926
Something we say
we always want to do,

07:36.018 --> 07:38.066
and we never do it,
so we're doing it.

07:38.151 --> 07:39.605
‐ Fun. Can I come?
‐ Yeah.

07:39.690 --> 07:40.899
You want to?

07:40.984 --> 07:43.275
‐ Yeah. ‐ I got an idea.
‐ Huh?

07:43.359 --> 07:45.261
Why don't you two go off
and make a day of it.

07:45.403 --> 07:46.964
‐ Just the two of you.
‐ Are you sure?

07:47.049 --> 07:49.409
Yeah. Carpe Diem Rebecca
is running me ragged.

07:49.499 --> 07:51.760
‐ (Kevin laughs) ‐ You just make
sure that you have her back in time

07:51.844 --> 07:52.879
for her doctor's appointment
at 4:30.

07:52.963 --> 07:54.298
‐ I can do that.
‐ Okay.

07:55.770 --> 07:58.481
